Usage: run Animation2.py -f filename -s source_vertex_number -t target_vertex_number -m
Usage: run AStarSearch.py -f filename -s source_vertex_number -t target_vertex_number -m

To plot network (usa map) over which path is plotted, include -m: (For usa network, this can take ~5 mins!)
run Animation2.py -f "usa.txt" -s 0 -t 69383 -m

To plot path without network, do not include -m:
run Animation2.py -f "usa.txt" -s 0 -t 69383

Number of vertices in network: 87575
Number of edges in network: 121961

File format of input text file:
number of vertices
number of edges
vertex_number x_coord y_coord
.... (continue for all vertices)
vertex_v vertex_w
... (continue for all edges)
blank line

# long path (between east coast and west coast) (default)
#source = 83494
#target = 35075

# short path
#source = 0
#target = 69383

#input6.txt
#source = 0
#target = 5

Movies of path search:
DijkstraSearch.mp4  - using dijstra's algorithm without a heuristic (14 mins!) (This is a mpeg4 video.)
AStarSearch.mp4 - using dijstra's algorithm with Euclidean heuristic (5 mins) (This is a mpeg4 video.)